Seven Bridges Advisors LLC Takes Position in Calpine Corp. (CPN)


Time:2016-10-03 01:00Turbochargers information Click:




 Calpine Corp. NYSE:CPN CPN Uti 
Seven Bridges Advisors LLC bought a new position in  Calpine Corp. (NYSE:CPN) during the second quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund bought 6,932 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $102,000. 
A number of other institutional investors have also recently modified their holdings of CPN. BlackRock Institutional Trust Company N.A. increased its position in shares of  Calpine Corp. by 14.9% in the first quarter. BlackRock Institutional Trust Company N.A. now owns 11,395,398 shares of the company’s stock worth $172,868,000 after buying an additional 1,482,027 shares during the period.  Renaissance Technologies LLC increased its position in shares of  Calpine Corp. by 90.3% in the first quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 2,567,700 shares of the company’s stock worth $38,952,000 after buying an additional 1,218,600 shares during the period.  Goldentree Asset Management LP increased its position in shares of  Calpine Corp. by 14.9% in the first quarter. Goldentree Asset Management LP now owns 5,715,155 shares of the company’s stock worth $86,699,000 after buying an additional 740,080 shares during the period.  Canada Pension Plan Investment Board increased its position in shares of  Calpine Corp. by 151.7% in the first quarter. Canada Pension Plan Investment Board now owns 1,191,706 shares of the company’s stock worth $18,078,000 after buying an additional 718,200 shares during the period.  Finally, Natixis increased its position in shares of  Calpine Corp. by 1,623.6% in the first quarter. Natixis now owns 693,922 shares of the company’s stock worth $10,527,000 after buying an additional 653,663 shares during the period. 92.67% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 
Calpine Corp. (NYSE:CPN) traded up 0.87% on Thursday, reaching $13.91. 3,090,510 shares of the company’s stock traded hands. The stock has a 50-day moving average of $12.88 and a 200 day moving average of $14.22. Calpine Corp. has a 52 week low of $11.53 and a 52 week high of $16.60. The firm’s market capitalization is $5.00 billion. 
Calpine Corp. (NYSE:CPN) last released its quarterly earnings results on Friday, July 29th. The company reported ($0.08) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of ($0.02) by $0.06. Calpine Corp. had a positive return on equity of 10.79% and a negative net margin of 0.02%. The firm had revenue of $1.16 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.29 billion. During the same period in the prior year, the business earned $0.09 earnings per share. Calpine Corp.’s revenue for the quarter was down 19.3% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, equities analysts expect that  Calpine Corp. will post $0.44 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
A number of equities analysts have commented on CPN shares. Deutsche Bank AG raised shares of Calpine Corp. from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and lifted their target price for the stock from $18.00 to $20.00 in a research note on Tuesday, July 26th. They noted that the move was a valuation call. SunTrust Banks Inc. reduced their price target on shares of Calpine Corp. from $14.00 to $13.00 and set a “neutral” rating on the stock in a research note on Wednesday, August 24th. Zacks Investment Research downgraded shares of Calpine Corp. from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research note on Tuesday, June 21st. BMO Capital Markets  reissued a “buy” rating on shares of Calpine Corp. in a research note on Wednesday, June 22nd. Finally, Royal Bank Of Canada  reissued a “buy” rating on shares of Calpine Corp. in a research note on Tuesday, May 31st. Three research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and nine have issued  a buy rating to the stock. The stock presently has an average rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $19.71.
In other news, Director Jack A. Fusco sold 24,800 shares of the stock in a transaction dated Monday, July 11th. The shares were sold at an average price of $14.75, for a total transaction of $365,800.00. Following the transaction, the director now directly owns 722,825 shares in the company, valued at approximately $10,661,668.75. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the SEC, which is available at this hyperlink. Also, Director Jack A. Fusco sold 54,600 shares of the stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, July 13th. The stock was sold at an average price of $15.00, for a total transaction of $819,000.00. Following the transaction, the director now owns 684,525 shares in the company, valued at $10,267,875. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Company insiders own  1.30% of the company’s stock. 
About Calpine Corp.
