Short description




We believe investment management poses a similarly unsolvable question. It is impossible to know which assets and strategies will have the best risk/return during any particular period, thus impossible to construct the ‘very best' portfolio for any environment. This can only be known ex-post with the benefit of perfect hindsight. Nevertheless, we undertake the process of asset allocation, strategy evaluation and manager selection to invest portfolios with what we believe are the best perceived risk/return characteristics. While no ‘right' answer can be found to the question of what assets to own at any one point in time, much is gleaned from the process of analyzing the problem. In our opinion, an investment portfolio, while never perfect, improves as we attempt to optimize risk/reward. As investors we are constantly learning, even though the problem is always 'unsolvable.'














