				Seven Bridges Advisors
	






























































































































Seven Bridges Advisors






Jun 2, 2013 @ 12:01 am
By 
	Liz Skinner























      Larry Cohen founded Seven Bridges Advisors LLC in 2011 to mix the investment strengths of the endowment model with the relationship benefits of a family office.  In two years, he's built the New York-based RIA up to nearly $2.5 billion in assets, serving high-net-worth individuals and institutions such as charities.  Seven Bridges Advisors, named after a middle school in Chappaqua, N.Y. — where Mr. Cohen raised his four sons — takes a research-based approach to investing, consistent with that of large endowments.
				



“The firm employs a deep bench of investment professionals who emphasize quantitative analysis and good judgment that comes with industry experience,” Mr. Co-hen said. The investment managers selected for clients use a variety of strategies and focus on different geographic sectors, along with investing in a wide range of securities. Seven Bridges doesn't group clients into standard asset allocation programs; instead, it customizes asset allocations for each. Mr. Cohen, a tax lawyer with a J.D. from Harvard Law School, sits on the board of directors for many nonprofits, including Brown University. He also is chairman of that university's investment committee.









